Egypt’s Radwan May Lose Job in Cabinet Reshuffle, Ahram Says

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-07-17T05:09:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/egypt-s-radwan-may-lose-job-in-cabinet-reshuffle-ahram-says.html
Finance Minister  Samir Radwan  faces
difficulties in keeping his job in  Egypt ’s new Cabinet because
of his ties to the dissolved  National Democratic Party , the
state-run Al Ahram newspaper reported, citing an unidentified
Cabinet official.  Fayza Aboulnaga, minister for planning and international
cooperation, may also not find a place in the Cabinet, the
Cairo-based newspaper quoted the official as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
 asalha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  